This article highlights the organizations representing doctors, nurses, and health care providers that are opposing the repeal of the Affordable Care Act. The American Nurses Association, American Medical Association, American Academy of Family Physicians, American College of Physicians, Association of American Medical Colleges, National Association of Community Health Centers, American Osteopathic Association, Catholic Health Association, American Public Health Association, Asian and Pacific Islander American Health Forum, Doctors for America, and National Hispanic Medical Association all support the Affordable Care Act. They believe that repealing the Act would have negative consequences on Americans' access to healthcare and would result in increasing costs and uninsured individuals. These organizations argue that the Affordable Care Act is an important step towards improving the health care system and ensuring affordable and accessible health care for all.